Date: Fri, 29 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] HID: ipts: bump IPTS_HID_REPORT_DATA_SIZE to 7488 to match descriptor

Commit 0a3fe972a7 made hid-core stricter: instead of zero-padding a HID report
that is shorter than its descriptor expects, it now returns -EINVAL. IPTS builds
report 65 at 7485 bytes, but the descriptor expects 7488 (1 id + 2 scan-time +
7485 data), so on EDS1 devices like the Surface Book 1 every frame is rejected
with "Failed to process buffer: -22" and touch stops working. Bump the size to
7488 to match.

Link: https://github.com/linux-surface/linux-surface/issues/2150
---
 drivers/hid/ipts/desc.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/hid/ipts/desc.h b/drivers/hid/ipts/desc.h
index 307438c..972a769 100644
--- a/drivers/hid/ipts/desc.h
+++ b/drivers/hid/ipts/desc.h
@@ -14,7 +14,7 @@
 #define IPTS_HID_REPORT_DATA	    65
 #define IPTS_HID_REPORT_SET_MODE    66
 
-#define IPTS_HID_REPORT_DATA_SIZE 7485
+#define IPTS_HID_REPORT_DATA_SIZE 7488
 
 /*
  * HID descriptor for singletouch data.
--
2.43.0
